Prediction, I think intel launches 10nm and starts to fall behind, but then comes out with their own chiplet design after that.

I'm not a diehard fan of either brand. Just my thoughts on the matter. It's too late into 10nm development to just launch it into the sun, and it takes too long for them to design a new chip to just jump onto chiplet. But I could easily see them scrapping whatever was next and imitating AMD. Unless there's a patent in the way, but there are ways around that.
